Installing ansibe :

sudo apt update [to check if machine is up to date]

sudo apt install software-properties-common

sudo apt-add-repository --yes --update ppa:ansible/ansible

sudo apt install ansible

~ lab start playbook-basic [sets up and ensures the environment is ready for the playbook to run]

~ lab finish playbook-basic [to conclude current exercise and previous resources do not affect upcoming resources]



! Basic commands:

vim filenmae.yml (ESC + :q! to exit vim editor) [to open vim editor]

nano filename.yml [to open a nano editor]

ansible-playbook filename.yml [to run playbook]

ansibe-playbook <filename.yml>--syntax-check [to check syntax errors]

ansibe-navigator run [to run playbook and name of the playbook is passed as an argument]



Docker Container:

docker run [to start a new docker  container from an image]
docker stop [to stop a running docker conatainer ID]
docker rm [to remove a docker conatainer]
docker ps [to list all the docker conatainers]
docker exec -it <container_ID> /bin/bash [accesing the container and id will be found when ps command is used]

Inventory:

~ ansible-navigator inventory [to verify a machines presence inside an inventory]
 ~ ansibe-navigator inventory -m stdout --list [to list all hosts]
 ~ ansibe-navigator inventory -m stdout --<group name>
 ~ ansibe-navigator.yml [to change default options for ansible-navigator command] 
 